 Extra Mural Lectures 201617

 presents

 "Bharatiya MukhabhinayaE2D

 a talk by

 Padmashri. Niranjan Goswami

 Mime Artist & Stage Director

 Date Saturday, 15th October

 Venue:CLT, IIT Madras

 Time: 5:00 pm



 Speaker Profile:



 Niranjan Goswami is a mime artist and stage director. One of the pioneers
 of mime in India, he is the founder and director of Indian Mime Theatre, 
a
 group promoting Mukhabhinaya, the art of silent acting. He is the first o
ne
 to direct full fledged plays in mime. A postgraduate in drama from Rabind
ra
 Bharathi University, he was awarded junior and senior fellowship by the
 Department of Culture, Government of India. He was awarded with the Sange
et
 Natak Akademi Award in 2002. For his innumerable contribution to Theatre,
 he was awarded the fourth highest civilian honour, Padma Shri in 2009 by
 Government of India. He is an active visiting professor at many
 universities including National School of Drama, New Delhi, Bharatendu
 Natya Academy, Lucknow, Film and Television Institute of India, Pune etc.
.



 We have also scheduled a mime workshop by Shri Niranjan Goswami on 1
5th
 of October in assistance from the Thespian Club.We hope it would be a 
wonderful
 learning opportunity for all of us and do sign up if you're interested. W
e
 have a limited capacity and hence its a registration only event. You can
 find the form here .We will
 inform the exact the timings later.


 PFA the event poster.


 Regards,

 The EML Team and Thespian Club





